NexPoint Multifamily Capital Trust, Inc.


A Disciplined Approach to Real Estate Investing
A Solution for All Real Estate Cycles
 
NexPoint Multifamily Capital Trust, Inc. (the “Company” or “NMCT”) is a non-traded Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT) that seeks to provide investors access to multifamily real estate investment opportunities in large cities and suburban markets of large cities, primarily in the Southeastern and Southwestern United States. We intend to directly or indirectly acquire, own, operate and selectively develop well-located Core Plus multifamily properties with a modest value-add component.
The Company’s primary investment objectives are (1) to provide current income for stockholders through the payment of cash distributions, (2) preserve and return stockholders’ capital contributions and (3) realize capital appreciation on the Company’s properties. NexPoint Multifamily Capital Trust provides investors an opportunity to invest in the growing American commercial real estate sector, more specifically in multifamily real property, through a professionally managed alternative investment vehicle managed by an investment firm with approximately $13.4 billion in assets under management and a specialized expertise in multifamily real estate investment.
Highland Capital Fund Distributors, Inc., member FINRA, is the dealer manager for the NexPoint Multifamily Capital Trust offering.
